FBIS3-6633 "dreas054__a94031" FBIS-EAS-94-054-A Document Type:Daily Report 21 March 1994 ANNEX Mongolia Opposition Leaders Consider Hural Participation OW1803194994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1717 GMT 18 Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1803194994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 18 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Five representatives of the oppositional parties of the country have decided to resume their participation in the activities of the Great State Hural if proposals forwarded by the president of the country at the opening ceremony of the autumn session of the Parliament would be accepted by the Parliament. Such a statement was made at the press conference by a member of the Great State Hural R. Gonchigdorj. He noted that the opposition in the Great State Hural are fighting not for power but in the interests of particular strata of the Mongolian public. According to him, the opposition parties would not abandon their democratic principles standing for the creation of a state structure to be acting in the interests of the whole people of Mongolia.
